</p><p id="Par38">where z<sub>&#x003b1;</sub>/2&#x02009;+&#x02009;z<sub>&#x003b2;</sub>&#x02009;=&#x02009;(1.96&#x02009;+&#x02009;0.84) assuming a power of 80% and 5% error.</p><p id="Par39">Considering the prevalence of near-miss haemorrhage equal to 2% in the comparison group, and assuming a <italic>k</italic> (the coefficient of the variation of the proportion of near misses between clusters) value of 0.15 [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR42">42</xref>], we calculated that the required number of clusters required is equal to 10 per group.<list list-type="bullet"><list-item><p id="Par40">
